#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.110:0.2"
msgid "11. Antavagga "
msgstr "11. Sides "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 110. Arahantasutta → arahaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.110:0.3"
msgid "110. Arahantasutta "
msgstr "110. A Perfected One "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn22.110:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.110:1.2"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, upādānakkhandhā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five grasping aggregates. "

msgctxt "sn22.110:1.3"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn22.110:1.4"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—rūpupādānakkhandho … pe … viññāṇupādānakkhandho. "
msgstr "That is, the grasping aggregates of form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn22.110:1.5"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imesaṃ pañcannaṃ upādānakkhandhānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā anupādāvimutto hoti. "
msgstr "A mendicant comes to be freed by not grasping after truly understanding these five grasping aggregates’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape. "

msgctxt "sn22.110:1.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto”ti. "
msgstr "Such a mendicant is called a perfected one, with defilements ended, who has completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is rightly freed through enlightenment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.110:1.7"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

